<main class="content"><article class="post-12640 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-announcements entry" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/CreativeWork"><header class="entry-header"><h1 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline">Corona Virus – Message from Superintendent Dr. Pam Vogel (3/12/2020)</h1>
</header><div class="entry-content" itemprop="text">
<p>Dear Parents, Students, Staff and Community Members,</p>



<p>As you are aware, the COVID-19 situation is ever-changing. Today, a message came out from the Governor’s Office and the Department of Education Commissioner’s Office with additional information regarding the increasing numbers of Coronavirus cases in Connecticut. Superintendents throughout the state then had an opportunity to ask more questions to seek additional information, as it impacts schools. Following that conversation, the superintendents in Litchfield County held another conference call to discuss the current circumstances in our part of the state. </p>



<p>We have not yet had a confirmed case in Region One. However, some of the schools that neighbor us have had confirmed cases in schools that are adjacent to them. For that reason, these schools have decided to cancel school for students beginning tomorrow.</p>



<p>In Region One, because we have not yet had confirmed cases, I would prefer that we hold school tomorrow, on Friday, for students and staff. This would allow time for our teachers and support staff to prepare materials to send home for the weeks to come. It will also provide more time for families to After consulting with local health officials, all of the schools in this area have agreed that, in the best interest of student and staff health and safety, our districts will be closed for at least two weeks.</p>



<p>We will use Friday as time to work with our students to prepare them for the learning that will need to take place in their homes. In the days ahead, our staff will be making every effort to stay in communication with families and students to determine if learning is progressing and will be offering additional support when needed, Our goal is to help students in every way we can. Every teacher will have communication with your students and with you tomorrow.</p>



<p>If any parent would prefer to not send their child to school tomorrow, please notify your child’s teacher and we will arrange a time to provide the materials that your student will need for the time ahead.</p>



<p>We will be having frequent communication with families about making food available to students. More information will be forthcoming next week.</p>



<p>Because tomorrow is our last school day for some time to come, we will be holding the Housatonic Musical Theater Society’s “Sound of Music” for one more evening at 7:30 PM.</p>



<p>We thank you for your understanding and do understand the challenges that this presents to everyone, We hope that we can all make the best of what are unprecedented and completely unforeseen circumstances. Please know that we will be available to reach out to, as you need.</p>



<p>Dr. Pam Vogel</p>



